    <text id="B0272T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>The law firm of Allen and Latson informs Jackson about the status of a case (of
                    unknown circumstances).</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr> JW Jordan,<lb/>Sub
                            <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst Comr</abbr> Bureau <abbr
                            expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R. F. &amp; A.
                        L.</abbr><lb/>Farmville, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-05-01">May 1, 1868</date>
                        <name type="place"><abbr expan="Washington">Wash<hi rend="super">n</hi></abbr>
                            D.C.</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Colonel:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>We have the honor to inform you that we have just <abbr expan="received">rec<hi
                            rend="super">d</hi></abbr>
                    <unclear>PWR's</unclear> check in favor of Edgar Allen, which we will remit to
                    you on receipt of our fee of $10, notwithstanding his repeated importunities to
                    send direct to him.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully Yours</salute>
                    <signed>Allen &amp; Latson</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">P.S. We would say that none of the other claims <abbr
                            expan="received">rec<hi rend="super">d</hi></abbr> from you have been
                        disposed of except as we have heretofore written you, A &amp; L</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
